                     <interp inst="def1-1507-18390513" type="given" value="FREDERICK"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">FREDERICK WALLER</hi>
                  </persName> was indicted<rs id="t18390513-1507-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18390513-1507-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18390513-1507-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="simpleLarceny"></interp> for stealing, on the <rs id="t18390513-cd-37" type="crimeDate">
                        <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18390513-1507-offence-1 t18390513-cd-37"></join>16th of April</rs>, 45 bottles, value 10<hi rend="italic">s</hi>., the property of <persName id="t18390513-name-258" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18390513-name-258" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390513-name-258" type="surname" value="TWYFORD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390513-name-258" type="given" value="SAMUEL"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18390513-1507-offence-1 t18390513-name-258"></join>Samuel Twyford, Esq</persName>.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390513-name-259" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390513-name-259" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390513-name-259" type="surname" value="FAIRLET"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390513-name-259" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS FAIRLET</persName>
                  </hi>. I am footman to Samuel Twyford, Esq., of Gloucester-place, Marylebone. About a quarter past six o'clock on the morning</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183905130028"></xptr>
               <p>of the 16th of April, I heard a noise in the area—I went and opened the door, and saw the prisoner within three steps of the top of the area, with a bottle in his hand—he went about three doors from the house and threw it down, smashed it, and ran away—I called "Stop thief"—I saw a man come down Gloucester-place—he stopped him—I gave him to the officer—I found a hamper in the area—the bottle-rack doors were both thrown open, and there were forty-four bottles in the basket, which had been taken out of the rack—the basket was not my master's, but the bottles were—when the policeman came down the area, the prisoner began to cry and said, "Let me go, I will never do so again—can you gave me a little water to drink?"</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390513-name-260" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390513-name-260" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390513-name-260" type="surname" value="THORPE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390513-name-260" type="given" value="ABRAHAM"></interp>ABRAHAM THORPE</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in Kingstone-street, Belgrave-square. I was in Gloucester-place, and heard the cry of "Stop thief"—the prisoner was coming up at the greatest speed—I caught and brought him back—he cried and said, "Pray let me go."</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390513-name-261" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390513-name-261" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390513-name-261" type="surname" value="KING"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390513-name-261" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS KING</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable D</hi> 74.) I took the prisoner in charge—these are the bottles.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> On the night before I met with a groom, he asked if I was a smith or a shoemaker—I said no, I was a wine-cooper—he said he knew of some bottles to sell—he took me to the area and counted them out—he heard a noise—he pushed me over the basket, and told me to run away.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390513-name-262" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390513-name-262" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390513-name-262" type="surname" value="FARLEY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390513-name-262" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS FARLEY</persName>
                  </hi>. I had unlocked the area gate about half-past six o'clock in the morning, as I always do—I saw a man running at the time the prisoner was, but I cannot say who he was—we have no groom.</p>
               <p>
